[
  "Henry Nicholas III and business partner Henry Samueli cofounded fabless semiconductor firm Broadcom in 1991 in a Redondo Beach, Calif. condominium.",
  "In February 2016 Broadcom was acquired by Singapore-based chip firm Avago for $37 billion in cash and stock and renamed Broadcom Ltd.",
  " Nicholas retired from Broadcom in 2003 but has held onto a nearly 3% stake in the company. ",
  "He's now focused on philanthropy and passing a crime victims' rights bill known as Marsy's Law, which is now law in 12 states. ",
  "In February 2019, Nicholas was charged with 5 counts of drug trafficking after police found heroin and methamphetamine in his Las Vegas hotel room in August. ",
  "In September 2019, he took a plea deal in his drug trafficking case. He'll attend drug counseling and donate $500,000 to area treatment centers. "
]